<br>
Plane of Fear is a rough zone...the golems you need to target have a death touch, and sometimes it seems like things in Fear aggro from across the zone.  I have not yet done this part of my epic, but my guild has helped other guilds with corpse runs from this zone.  <br>
<br>
Getting to the Spiroc Lord will also take quite some time, and he has a death touch as well. Plane of Air is also tricky in a number of ways...make sure you research this zone carefully before attempting it, or you're going to have some very difficult corpse runs.<br>
<br>
I don't know about the Hand of the Maestro.  I'm still trying to find out myself if you need to kill the Maestro to get to the Hand, or if it's a totally independent spawn.  If you need to deal with the Maestro first, no way a single group can handle it.<br>
<br>
Best bet is to get a raid force together for all of these. (And BTW...I have yet to see a pick-up raid in Fear end in anything other than corpse runs.  When you go to Fear make sure you know who you're depending on...make sure you know their playing style, etc.)<br>
<br>
Hope all this helps....I know it sounds discouraging.  Good luck!<br>
